modules.description: This module tracks a generation counter and provides functions to manage values tied to specific generations. It allows wrapping a value with the current generation, extracting the original value, and conditionally applying functions based on generation equality. Use it to implement versioning or change tracking in stateful systems, ensuring operations only affect values from the current generation.

This module manages event channels for interdomain communication in a virtualized environment. It provides operations to create, bind, notify, and close event channels, along with checking their validity. Concrete use cases include setting up event-driven communication between virtual domains or handling domain exception interrupts.
